# Battle of porto bello

#REDIRECT Battle of Porto Bello (1739)

---

## Battle of Porto Bello

The Battle of Porto Bello may refer to:
* Capture of Porto Bello (1601), was an engagement of the Anglo-Spanish War (1585–1604)
* Henry Morgan's raid on Porto Bello (1668), by Welsh privateer Henry Morgan
* Assault on Porto Bello (1680), by buccaneer John Coxon
* Attack on Porto Bello (1702), was an engagement of the War of the Spanish Succession
* Blockade of Porto Bello (1726–1728), was an engagement of the Anglo-Spanish War (1727–1729)
* Battle of Porto Bello (1739), was an engagement of the War of Jenkins' Ear
* Porto Bello Fiasco (1742), was an expedition of the War of Jenkins' Ear
* Bombardment of Porto Bello (1744), was an action of the War of Jenkins' Ear
* Attack on Porto Bello (1814), was an engagement of the Spanish American wars of independence
* Attack on Porto Bello (1819), was an engagement of the Spanish American wars of independence
